      MATCH (n)-[:REL]->(m)
      RETURN m.id AS id
      ORDER BY id LIMIT 1
      """
    Then the result should be, in order:
      | id |
      | 1  |
    And no side effects

  Scenario: Limit before distinct
    And having executed:
      """
      CREATE (:A {id:0})-[:REL]->(:B {id:1})
      """
    When executing query:
      """
      MATCH (n:A) WITH n LIMIT 1
      MATCH (n)-[:REL]->(m)
      RETURN DISTINCT m.id AS id
      """
    Then the result should be, in order:
